# Project Structure Guide

## Overview

This is a React + TypeScript project called "Who Knows U" - a WhatsApp chat opener tool that allows users to send messages without adding contacts.

## Main Entry Points

- [App.tsx](mdc:src/App.tsx) - Main application component
- [main.tsx](mdc:src/main.tsx) - Application entry point
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - HTML entry point

## Project Structure

### Source Organization

- `src/components/` - React components (e.g., [Footer.tsx](mdc:src/components/Footer.tsx))
- `src/data/` - Static data and constants (e.g., [countries-phone.ts](mdc:src/data/countries-phone.ts))
- `src/utils/` - Utility functions (e.g., [validateNumberPhone.ts](mdc:src/utils/validateNumberPhone.ts))
- `src/types.d.ts` - Type definitions
- `src/index.css` - Global styles and Tailwind imports

### Configuration Files

- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path aliases
- [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts) - Vite build configuration with Tailwind plugin
- [.eslintrc.json](mdc:.eslintrc.json) - ESLint configuration
- [.prettierrc.json](mdc:.prettierrc.json) - Prettier configuration

### Key Features

- WhatsApp link generation for direct messaging
- Country phone code selector
- Phone number validation
- Spanish language support (documentation and UI)
- Tailwind CSS v4 with @theme configuration
- Fontsource fonts (DynaPuff and Poppins)
- Self-hosted fonts for better privacy and performance

### Path Aliases

- Use `@/` prefix to import from `src/` directory (e.g., `@/components/Footer`)
- Configured in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json)
